WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.820 --> 00:00:14.820
Embracing otherness.
拥抱他人

2
00:00:14.820 --> 00:00:16.820
When I first heard this theme,
当我第一次听到这个主题时

3
00:00:16.820 --> 00:00:18.820
I thought, well, embracing otherness
我觉得拥抱他人

4
00:00:18.820 --> 00:00:21.820
is embracing myself.
就是拥抱我自己

5
00:00:21.820 --> 00:00:23.820
And the journey to that place
对于我来说

6
00:00:23.820 --> 00:00:25.820
of understanding and acceptance
通往理解和接纳的路

7
00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:28.820
has been an interesting one for me,
是十分有意思的

8
00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:30.820
and it's given me an insight
并且让我对“自我”这一概念

9
00:00:30.820 --> 00:00:32.820
into the whole notion of self,
有了深刻的理解

10
00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:36.820
which I think is worth sharing with you today.
我想这值得在今天和你们分享

11
00:00:36.820 --> 00:00:38.820
We each have a self,
我们都有一个自我

12
00:00:38.820 --> 00:00:41.820
but I don't think that we're born with one.
但我并不认为这是与生俱来的

13
00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:43.820
You know how newborn babies
你看那些刚出生的小婴儿

14
00:00:43.820 --> 00:00:45.820
believe they're part of everything;
他们认为自己属于任何事物

15
00:00:45.820 --> 00:00:47.820
they're not separate?
他们并不是脱离的

16
00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:50.820
Well that fundamental sense of oneness
这种最基本的同一性

17
00:00:50.820 --> 00:00:52.820
is lost on us very quickly.
会很快从我们身上消失

18
00:00:52.820 --> 00:00:54.820
It's like that initial stage is over --
如同最初始的状态已经结束

19
00:00:54.820 --> 00:00:56.820
oneness: infancy,
同一性：婴儿期

20
00:00:56.820 --> 00:00:58.820
unformed, primitive.
未成形的，原始的

21
00:00:58.820 --> 00:01:01.820
It's no longer valid or real.
将不复存在

22
00:01:01.820 --> 00:01:03.820
What is real is separateness,
取而代之的是分离

23
00:01:03.820 --> 00:01:05.820
and at some point in early babyhood,
在婴儿期的某一点

24
00:01:05.820 --> 00:01:07.820
the idea of self
关于自我的意识

25
00:01:07.820 --> 00:01:09.820
starts to form.
开始萌芽

26
00:01:09.820 --> 00:01:12.820
Our little portion of oneness is given a name,
我们同一性的一小部分被赋予了一个名字

27
00:01:12.820 --> 00:01:15.820
is told all kinds of things about itself,
被告知关于它自己的任何事情

28
00:01:15.820 --> 00:01:17.820
and these details,
这些细节

29
00:01:17.820 --> 00:01:19.820
opinions and ideas
观点和想法

30
00:01:19.820 --> 00:01:21.820
become facts,
变成事实

31
00:01:21.820 --> 00:01:23.820
which go towards building ourselves,
这些都帮我们形成自我

32
00:01:23.820 --> 00:01:25.820
our identity.
以及自己的身份

33
00:01:25.820 --> 00:01:27.820
And that self becomes the vehicle
然后这个自我就成为一个工具

34
00:01:27.820 --> 00:01:30.820
for navigating our social world.
用来探索周围的这个世界

35
00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:33.820
But the self is a projection
但是这个自我实际上是一个投影

36
00:01:33.820 --> 00:01:35.820
based on other people's projections.
以其他人的投影为基础

37
00:01:35.820 --> 00:01:38.820
Is it who we really are?
这就是真正的我们吗？

38
00:01:38.820 --> 00:01:41.820
Or who we really want to be, or should be?
是我们真正想成为，或者应该成为的人吗？

39
00:01:41.820 --> 00:01:44.820
So this whole interaction
在我成长过程中

40
00:01:44.820 --> 00:01:46.820
with self and identity
我一直都很难处理

41
00:01:46.820 --> 00:01:48.820
was a very difficult one for me growing up.
自我与身份之间的相互影响

42
00:01:48.820 --> 00:01:51.820
The self that I attempted to take out into the world
那个我尝试着向周围的世界展示的自我

43
00:01:51.820 --> 00:01:54.820
was rejected over and over again.
被一次又一次拒绝

44
00:01:54.820 --> 00:01:56.820
And my panic
因为没有一个合适的自我

45
00:01:56.820 --> 00:01:58.820
at not having a self that fit,
而带来的恐慌

46
00:01:58.820 --> 00:02:00.820
and the confusion that came
以及因为被拒绝

47
00:02:00.820 --> 00:02:02.820
from my self being rejected,
而产生的惶恐

48
00:02:02.820 --> 00:02:05.820
created anxiety, shame
引起了我的焦虑，羞愧

49
00:02:05.820 --> 00:02:07.820
and hopelessness,
还有无望

50
00:02:07.820 --> 00:02:10.820
which kind of defined me for a long time.
这些在很长一段时间里都限制了我

51
00:02:10.820 --> 00:02:12.820
But in retrospect,
但当我回想过去

52
00:02:12.820 --> 00:02:15.820
the destruction of my self was so repetitive
对于自我的毁灭反复出现

53
00:02:15.820 --> 00:02:17.820
that I started to see a pattern.
我开始看出一些规律

54
00:02:17.820 --> 00:02:20.820
The self changed,
一个自我被改变

55
00:02:20.820 --> 00:02:23.820
got affected, broken, destroyed,
被影响，被打击破坏

56
00:02:23.820 --> 00:02:26.820
but another one would evolve --
但有一个新的会形成

57
00:02:26.820 --> 00:02:28.820
sometimes stronger,
有时更强

58
00:02:28.820 --> 00:02:30.820
sometimes hateful,
有时充满仇恨

59
00:02:30.820 --> 00:02:32.820
sometimes not wanting to be there at all.
有时则根本不想出现

60
00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:35.820
The self was not constant.
这个自我并不是恒定的

61
00:02:36.820 --> 00:02:38.820
And how many times
在我还没有意识到

62
00:02:38.820 --> 00:02:40.820
would my self have to die
这个自我曾经从未存在时

63
00:02:40.820 --> 00:02:42.820
before I realized
我的“自我”

64
00:02:42.820 --> 00:02:45.820
that it was never alive in the first place?
会死多少次呢？

65
00:02:45.820 --> 00:02:47.820
I grew up on the coast of England
我于上世纪七十年代

66
00:02:47.820 --> 00:02:49.820
in the '70s.
生长在英格兰的海岸边

67
00:02:49.820 --> 00:02:52.820
My dad is white from Cornwall,
我父亲是来自康沃尔的白人

68
00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:56.820
and my mom is black from Zimbabwe.
我母亲是来自津巴布韦的黑人

69
00:02:56.820 --> 00:02:58.820
Even the idea of us as a family
对于许多人来说

70
00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:01.820
was challenging to most people.
是无论如何也想不到我们是一家人

71
00:03:01.820 --> 00:03:03.820
But nature had its wicked way,
但大自然自有意想不到的一面

72
00:03:03.820 --> 00:03:05.820
and brown babies were born.
棕色的孩子出生了

73
00:03:05.820 --> 00:03:07.820
But from about the age of five,
但自从五岁开始

74
00:03:07.820 --> 00:03:10.820
I was aware that I didn't fit.
我就察觉出我的格格不入

75
00:03:10.820 --> 00:03:13.820
I was the black atheist kid
我是一个信奉无神论的黑人孩子

76
00:03:13.820 --> 00:03:16.820
in the all-white Catholic school run by nuns.
在一个由修女运转的白人天主学校

77
00:03:16.820 --> 00:03:18.820
I was an anomaly,
我是一个另类

78
00:03:18.820 --> 00:03:22.820
and my self was rooting around for definition
我的自我在不断寻找一个定义

79
00:03:22.820 --> 00:03:25.820
and trying to plug in.
并试图将自己套入定义

80
00:03:25.820 --> 00:03:27.820
Because the self likes to fit,
因为自我都是愿意去融入

81
00:03:27.820 --> 00:03:29.820
to see itself replicated,
看到自己被复制

82
00:03:29.820 --> 00:03:31.820
to belong.
有归属感

83
00:03:31.820 --> 00:03:33.820
That confirms its existence
那能确认自我的存在感

84
00:03:33.820 --> 00:03:35.820
and its importance.
和重要性

85
00:03:35.820 --> 00:03:37.820
And it is important.
这很重要

86
00:03:37.820 --> 00:03:39.820
It has an extremely important function.
这有一个极端重要的功能

87
00:03:39.820 --> 00:03:43.820
Without it, we literally can't interface with others.
没有一个对自我的定义，我们简直不能和其他人交流

88
00:03:43.820 --> 00:03:45.820
We can't hatch plans
我们无法制定计划

89
00:03:45.820 --> 00:03:48.820
and climb that stairway of popularity,
无法爬上潮流和成功

90
00:03:48.820 --> 00:03:50.820
of success.
的阶梯

91
00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:53.820
But my skin color wasn't right.
但我的肤色不对

92
00:03:53.820 --> 00:03:55.820
My hair wasn't right.
我的发色不对

93
00:03:55.820 --> 00:03:57.820
My history wasn't right.
我的来历不对

94
00:03:57.820 --> 00:03:59.820
My self became defined
我的自我

95
00:03:59.820 --> 00:04:01.820
by otherness,
被他人定义

96
00:04:01.820 --> 00:04:03.820
which meant that, in that social world,
这意味着在社会上

97
00:04:03.820 --> 00:04:05.820
I didn't really exist.
我并不存在

98
00:04:05.820 --> 00:04:08.820
And I was "other" before being anything else --
我首先被定义为一个另类

99
00:04:08.820 --> 00:04:11.820
even before being a girl.
甚至先于被定义为一个女孩

100
00:04:11.820 --> 00:04:14.820
I was a noticeable nobody.
我是一个引人注意的没有人

101
00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:17.820
Another world was opening up
在这个时候

102
00:04:17.820 --> 00:04:19.820
around this time:
另一个世界出现了

103
00:04:19.820 --> 00:04:22.820
performance and dancing.
那就是表演和舞蹈

104
00:04:22.820 --> 00:04:25.820
That nagging dread of self-hood
对于自我纠缠不清的恐惧

105
00:04:25.820 --> 00:04:28.820
didn't exist when I was dancing.
在我跳舞时并不存在

106
00:04:28.820 --> 00:04:31.820
I'd literally lose myself.
我像是失去了自己

107
00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:34.820
And I was a really good dancer.
我是一个好的舞蹈演员

108
00:04:34.820 --> 00:04:36.820
I would put
我会把

109
00:04:36.820 --> 00:04:38.820
all my emotional expression
我所有的感情

110
00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:40.820
into my dancing.
投入到舞蹈中去

111
00:04:40.820 --> 00:04:43.820
I could be in the movement
在舞蹈中

112
00:04:43.820 --> 00:04:45.820
in a way that I wasn't able to be
我能完成我在现实中

113
00:04:45.820 --> 00:04:48.820
in my real life, in myself.
自己无法做到的动作

114
00:04:48.820 --> 00:04:50.820
And at 16,
当我16岁时

115
00:04:50.820 --> 00:04:53.820
I stumbled across another opportunity,
我无意中遇到另一个机遇

116
00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:57.820
and I earned my first acting role in a film.
得到了我的第一个电影角色

117
00:04:57.820 --> 00:04:59.820
I can hardly find the words
我难以找到言语

118
00:04:59.820 --> 00:05:02.820
to describe the peace I felt
来形容在表演中

119
00:05:02.820 --> 00:05:04.820
when I was acting.
我感受到的平静

120
00:05:04.820 --> 00:05:06.820
My dysfunctional self
我那残缺的自我

121
00:05:06.820 --> 00:05:08.820
could actually plug in
终于融入了

122
00:05:08.820 --> 00:05:10.820
to another self, not my own,
不是我自己的另一个自我

123
00:05:10.820 --> 00:05:13.820
and it felt so good.
这种感觉真好

124
00:05:13.820 --> 00:05:15.820
It was the first time that I existed
那是我第一次存在于

125
00:05:15.820 --> 00:05:18.820
inside a fully-functioning self --
一个正常运作的自我

126
00:05:18.820 --> 00:05:21.820
one that I controlled,
一个我可以控制的

127
00:05:21.820 --> 00:05:23.820
that I steered,
可以操纵的

128
00:05:23.820 --> 00:05:26.820
that I gave life to.
可以赋予生命的自我

129
00:05:26.820 --> 00:05:28.820
But the shooting day would end,
但是拍摄的日子终会结束

130
00:05:28.820 --> 00:05:30.820
and I'd return
我也会回到

131
00:05:30.820 --> 00:05:33.820
to my gnarly, awkward self.
我那扭曲尴尬的自我

132
00:05:33.820 --> 00:05:36.820
By 19,
当我19岁时

133
00:05:36.820 --> 00:05:38.820
I was a fully-fledged movie actor,
我已经是一个羽翼丰满的电影演员

134
00:05:38.820 --> 00:05:41.820
but still searching for definition.
但却仍在寻找定义

135
00:05:41.820 --> 00:05:43.820
I applied to read anthropology
我在大学里

136
00:05:43.820 --> 00:05:45.820
at university.
申请攻读人类学

137
00:05:45.820 --> 00:05:48.820
Dr. Phyllis Lee gave me my interview,
Phyllis Lee博士对我进行了面试

138
00:05:48.820 --> 00:05:52.820
and she asked me, "How would you define race?"
她问我：“你怎样定义种族？”

139
00:05:52.820 --> 00:05:54.820
Well, I thought I had the answer to that one,
嗯，我觉得我有答案

140
00:05:54.820 --> 00:05:57.820
and I said, "Skin color."
然后我说：“肤色。”

141
00:05:57.820 --> 00:06:01.820
"So biology, genetics?" she said.
她继续问道：“也就是生物学基因上的差异？”

142
00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:03.820
"Because, Thandie, that's not accurate.
“因为，桑迪，肤色并不准确。

143
00:06:03.820 --> 00:06:06.820
Because there's actually more genetic difference
在一个黑皮肤的肯尼亚人

144
00:06:06.820 --> 00:06:08.820
between a black Kenyan
和一个黑皮肤的乌干达人

145
00:06:08.820 --> 00:06:10.820
and a black Ugandan
之间存在的基因差异

146
00:06:10.820 --> 00:06:13.820
than there is between a black Kenyan
实际上超过在一个黑皮肤的肯尼亚人

147
00:06:13.820 --> 00:06:15.820
and, say, a white Norwegian.
和一个，比如说，白皮肤的挪威人之间的差异

148
00:06:15.820 --> 00:06:17.820
Because we all stem from Africa.
因为我们都起源于非洲

149
00:06:17.820 --> 00:06:19.820
So in Africa,
所以在非洲

150
00:06:19.820 --> 00:06:21.820
there's been more time
更有可能产生

151
00:06:21.820 --> 00:06:23.820
to create genetic diversity."
基因多样性。”

152
00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:25.820
In other words,
换句话说

153
00:06:25.820 --> 00:06:27.820
race has no basis
种族这一说法

154
00:06:27.820 --> 00:06:30.820
in biological or scientific fact.
并没有生物学或科学基础

155
00:06:30.820 --> 00:06:33.820
On the one hand, result.
一方面，这是结果

156
00:06:33.820 --> 00:06:35.820
Right?
对吗？

157
00:06:35.820 --> 00:06:38.820
On the other hand, my definition of self
另一方面，我对自我的定义

158
00:06:38.820 --> 00:06:41.820
just lost a huge chunk of its credibility.
则失去了相当大一部分的可信度

159
00:06:41.820 --> 00:06:43.820
But what was credible,
可以相信的

160
00:06:43.820 --> 00:06:46.820
what is biological and scientific fact,
以及生物学和科学事实

161
00:06:46.820 --> 00:06:49.820
is that we all stem from Africa --
就是我们都起源于非洲

162
00:06:49.820 --> 00:06:52.820
in fact, from a woman called Mitochondrial Eve
实际上，起源于一个叫做线粒体夏娃的女人

163
00:06:52.820 --> 00:06:55.820
who lived 160,000 years ago.
她生活在十六万年前

164
00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:58.820
And race is an illegitimate concept
种族是一个不合法的概念

165
00:06:58.820 --> 00:07:00.820
which our selves have created
是我们自己创造出来的

166
00:07:00.820 --> 00:07:04.820
based on fear and ignorance.
基于恐惧和无知

167
00:07:04.820 --> 00:07:06.820
Strangely, these revelations
奇怪的是，这些启示

168
00:07:06.820 --> 00:07:09.820
didn't cure my low self-esteem,
并没有治愈我那缺少的自尊

169
00:07:09.820 --> 00:07:12.820
that feeling of otherness.
那种被划为另类的感觉

170
00:07:12.820 --> 00:07:14.820
My desire to disappear
我渴望消失的想法

171
00:07:14.820 --> 00:07:16.820
was still very powerful.
依旧十分强烈

172
00:07:16.820 --> 00:07:18.820
I had a degree from Cambridge;
我有一个剑桥的学位

173
00:07:18.820 --> 00:07:20.820
I had a thriving career,
我的事业蒸蒸日上

174
00:07:20.820 --> 00:07:23.820
but my self was a car crash,
但我的自我却如同一场车祸

175
00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:25.820
and I wound up with bulimia
最终我患上贪食症

176
00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:27.820
and on a therapist's couch.
并接受治疗

177
00:07:27.820 --> 00:07:29.820
And of course I did.
我当然会这样

178
00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:31.820
I still believed
我依旧相信

179
00:07:31.820 --> 00:07:33.820
my self was all I was.
我的自我就是我的全部

180
00:07:33.820 --> 00:07:35.820
I still valued self-worth
我依旧认为自我价值

181
00:07:35.820 --> 00:07:37.820
above all other worth,
高于其余任何价值

182
00:07:37.820 --> 00:07:40.820
and what was there to suggest otherwise?
不然还能怎样呢？

183
00:07:40.820 --> 00:07:42.820
We've created entire value systems
我们创造了整个价值系统

184
00:07:42.820 --> 00:07:44.820
and a physical reality
以及一个客观的现实

185
00:07:44.820 --> 00:07:46.820
to support the worth of self.
用以支持自我的价值

186
00:07:46.820 --> 00:07:48.820
Look at the industry for self-image
看看由个人形象带动的产业

187
00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:50.820
and the jobs it creates,
还有它提供的工作

188
00:07:50.820 --> 00:07:53.820
the revenue it turns over.
以及它创造的价值

189
00:07:53.820 --> 00:07:55.820
We'd be right in assuming
我们可能会假设

190
00:07:55.820 --> 00:07:57.820
that the self is an actual living thing.
这个自我是真实存在的

191
00:07:57.820 --> 00:08:00.820
But it's not. It's a projection
但我们错了；这只是一个投影

192
00:08:00.820 --> 00:08:02.820
which our clever brains create
是由我们聪明的大脑创造出来的

193
00:08:02.820 --> 00:08:04.820
in order to cheat ourselves
来欺骗我们自己

194
00:08:04.820 --> 00:08:07.820
from the reality of death.
无需面对死亡的现实

195
00:08:08.820 --> 00:08:10.820
But there is something
但总有一些事

196
00:08:10.820 --> 00:08:12.820
that can give the self
能赋予自我

197
00:08:12.820 --> 00:08:15.820
